driver_attach():
struct device_driver *drv = ...;
struct device *dev = ...;

if (driver_attach(dev, drv)) {
    /* driver successfully attached */
}

The kernel maintains device lists and traverses them when needed. When a driver claims a device, the device is removed from the free list and added to the driver's list. When device_release() is called, the device is removed from all lists and can be safely freed.

